text: Lenka Kopčová (born 3 November 1999) is a Slovak footballer who plays as a forward and has appeared for the Slovakia women's national team. ==Career== Kopčová has been capped for the Slovakia national team, appearing for the team during the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup qualifying cycle. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Slovak women's footballers Category:Slovakia women's international footballers Category:Women's association football forwards Category:FC Slovan Liberec players Category:Expatriate women's footballers in the Czech Republic Category:Slovak expatriate sportspeople in the Czech Republic
